<br>
I am not so much looking for strategy on a specific encounter, but just good practices for the raiders and how to lead a successfully raid.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your help<br>
<br>
Alaar Everstar<br>
49th Enchanter<br>
&lt;Spirit Pack&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueoralsolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EoralSolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 565<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 9:44:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Raid walk thoughs</span><hr size=1> Some lessons I have learned in no particular order, take them for what they are and hopefully they wont all be wrong<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Patience is the best trait of the beginning raid leader.  As you get experience, and as you develop a crew that you are comfortable with and who know what to do, you can delegate more and keep yourself sane.  Til then, be patient with all the mistakes, stay happy, and enjoy being in charge.<br>
<br>
Protect your clerics.  Make sure you have enough, make sure they know when they need to camp out, and make sure they wont bail on you mid raid.<br>
<br>
Have lots of secondary heal mojo, (Druids, Shamans, Paladins) and teach people how to assist heal)  All groups should have to pcs who can heal.<br>
<br>
Protect your CC.  Levels are better than classes.  If you are doing Fear and have a lev 49 chanter and a level 55 Bard..the Bard is CC.  <br>
<br>
Buff groups&gt;buff circles.  Have a group, preferably with a bard, and have them in charge of buffing everyone with whatever is availble. STA, STR, AC, HP, C1-3, Haste, resistant buffs...toss em around as the stronger the raid the stronger the raid...<br>
<br>
A mana battery or 3 is a good thing.<br>
<br>
Main tanks...love em.  Second Tanks...love em too)<br>
<br>
Offensive CC is fun!  4 spite golems with 4 tanks each on one works just fine...or 3 tanks on 3 spiroc vanquishers..or whatever)<br>
<br>
You will personaly kill your friends many many times.   Dont worry about it, they will still love you.<br>
<br>
Bite off more than you can chew...you wont learn if you dont.<br>
<br>
Fear nothing, or you wont learn.  But dont be foolish, or it will hurt.<br>
<br>
Respect other raids.  If you are first assert yourself, but if it is a conflict, ask yourself is a fight worth it, or is the are back up raid you can do that will be just as fun?<br>
<br>
Always have a back up raid: if you want to do reavers in CoMand they are camped, go to seb and to do reets and juggs)  Content works for you.<br>
<br>
Peridots and pearls are needed, always have a bag on you.  Dont be cheap, if you have the buffs you dont wish you had em.  When in doubt, rune iv the entire raid)<br>
<br>
Keep all cash, raids cost money, plus it is nice being rich.<br>
<br>
Make some loot rules, it keeps everyone happy.<br>
<br>
Enforce em TO THE LETTER, it keeps everyone happy.<br>
<br>
Dont put up with any BS about loot, even from friends and guildmates, you will be respected.<br>
<br>
Remember, when you are done you turn off the machine, and it is just a game.<br>
<br>
Eoral<br>
Khan of the Chixom<br>
